<body>
    <h1>Get Departments</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"a179e9ea4c86"><strong>Component type:</strong> Actio=
n</p>
<p local-id=3D"0b3072b1e444"><strong>Category:</strong> Property Configurat=
ion</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"9b809bb2ac4b" id=3D"GetDepartments-Overview">Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"4b70cd38388f">The <strong>Get Departments</strong> action re=
trieves all the departments configured for your property (e.g., Housekeepin=
g, Maintenance, Front Office). Departments represent the organizational uni=
ts within your property that can be assigned to tasks and other operational=
 items in Mews Operations.</p>
<p local-id=3D"162661170b85">This component requires no input fields =E2=80=
=94 it automatically retrieves all active departments for the connected pro=
perty. The component outputs a list of departments on the <strong>out</stro=
ng> port, where each item contains a unique identifier and a display name. =
This is commonly used as a helper step within a workflow to provide a list =
of available departments for downstream actions or conditions =E2=80=94 for=
 example, to assign a department when creating a task, or to route workflow=
 logic based on the department involved.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"7631c264-cb9f-4ee0-ba6b-78ba3b03fa4c">
<h2 local-id=3D"673842f4f0d2" id=3D"GetDepartments-InputFields">Input Field=
s</h2>
<p local-id=3D"6fc68c5a6c6c">This component has no input fields. It automat=
ically retrieves all departments configured for the property associated wit=
h the connected Mews account.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"7983fbc8-8894-47d3-92dd-2ccc1dc2df6c">
<h2 local-id=3D"4df6edc9c60e" id=3D"GetDepartments-OutputFields">Output Fie=
lds</h2>
<p local-id=3D"60e1b6a6c300">When the departments are successfully retrieve=
d, the following values are available on the <strong>out</strong> output po=
rt as an array called <strong>Items</strong>. Each item in the array contai=
ns:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"a52643e6-feae-468a-964d-7a5=
342176599" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d6d35980-ab34-4c49-8939-d92911f85a4a">
<th data-local-id=3D"a997de8a-5f1f-44e6-9694-8b342692f5f7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ffd487d88a9d">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"8c3a78fc-152d-4a9a-93f0-a312d58dbea1" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"152f421afbd2">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"d2cf3c57-97a9-4024-b1c5-40776e9a375b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"be22aecfc75a">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"e76aa907-fb3e-46d5-80c0-1ea167bd4dcb">
<td data-local-id=3D"ba4ef152-057b-40e8-9b48-1e6d892fc79f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dde27113f4a5"><strong>Value</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9bf96a8e-89b4-4b15-9c6f-1a1353e363ef" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c5a0741e430d">Text (GUID)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f2504b2d-847e-46b7-b670-bdad8fbf8781" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"724c210dcabe">The unique identifier of the department. This =
ID can be used in subsequent workflow steps to reference a specific departm=
ent =E2=80=94 for example, when assigning a department to a new task.</p></=
td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2c6685e1-33fe-46ff-8c87-0b62aefbf716">
<td data-local-id=3D"c82f4590-34ed-423b-994d-32a9c0919d6d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c54f6fe29a8f"><strong>Label</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a42d4945-6559-454a-8efe-41674b24b915" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"78e505542b83">Text</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7bd5578d-6b73-4771-8ae3-557623b0169c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9cf5867bee4f">The display name of the department as configur=
ed in your property settings (e.g., "Housekeeping", "Maintenance", "Front O=
ffice").</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"928836d6a1d6"><strong>Note:</strong> The results are sorted =
alphabetically by the department name to make it easier to find specific de=
partments in the list.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"42848c23-787d-4344-82b0-17d71655794f">
<h2 local-id=3D"76fdf39d4f4a" id=3D"GetDepartments-HowItWorks">How It Works=
</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"3c8ef84f-7665-4adf-b442-8e722fdd6933">
<li local-id=3D"59d14596-df86-4a68-8650-adaff6311ca6">
<p local-id=3D"bf68b9927746">The component is triggered by a previous step =
in the workflow (no input configuration is needed).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f83d81ec-8c05-43ea-8c16-5615e107c087">
<p local-id=3D"e657e69d8fda">A request is sent to retrieve all active depar=
tments for the property associated with the connected Mews account.</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"0af27e2b-507a-4203-8fa5-dc222f4871e2">
<p local-id=3D"edd2bc9a91cf">Only active departments are included =E2=80=94=
 any departments that have been deactivated or deleted in your property set=
tings are excluded from the results.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c529972d-0f37-4d7c-b170-db4f93e0d878">
<p local-id=3D"c4d0c1f8e1ea">Each department is mapped to a label (display =
name) and value (unique ID), sorted alphabetically by name.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3fcaf841-71d4-4624-96b6-47bf5f78548d">
<p local-id=3D"c758dffe50e8">The list of departments is sent to the <strong=
>out</strong> output port as an array of items.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"84a1c06f-26b3-4757-9833-12714c569eb3">
<h2 local-id=3D"57bb07455e42" id=3D"GetDepartments-ExampleUseCases">Example=
 Use Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"9155a9c5-0871-46ce-b224-4a70fce94562">
<li local-id=3D"fa83c907-9d00-40c5-b3fe-cd9e80471954">
<p local-id=3D"7f284faa1bb0"><strong>Task assignment</strong> =E2=80=94 Use=
 Get Departments to retrieve the list of departments, then use the departme=
nt ID in a subsequent <strong>Add Task</strong> action to assign the newly =
created task to a specific department (e.g., Housekeeping).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c3b035f9-fd09-4562-a322-505b1a427461">
<p local-id=3D"e61630ecac8a"><strong>Department-based routing</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Retrieve all departments and use them in a conditional step to apply=
 different workflow logic depending on which department is involved (e.g., =
route maintenance requests to one flow and housekeeping requests to another=
).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"25828140-890d-470a-97cb-56794c3b7b49">
<p local-id=3D"4aeae46999f5"><strong>Dropdown population</strong> =E2=80=94=
 Provide a dynamic list of departments as selectable options in other compo=
nents that accept a department input, ensuring the options always reflect t=
he current property configuration.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"f6c374d1-bd39-44b8-8927-4ba261100794">
<h2 local-id=3D"d1da6742a01f" id=3D"GetDepartments-Caching">Caching</h2>
<p local-id=3D"17d39094e0d5">The results of this component are cached to im=
prove performance. Departments are relatively static data that does not cha=
nge frequently. If you have recently added or modified departments in your =
property settings, there may be a short delay before the updated department=
s appear in the component's output.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
